                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d356">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.512/3116: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-02-16T09:00:00-07:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 16, 1924—9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>82. Following from American consul at Guadalajara: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“February 14, 5 p.m. State authorities have issued a decree requiring the
                            payment of taxes December, February inclusive, which the revolutionary
                            government exacted while in power. What shall I advise American citizens
                            as to repayment of these?”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
